summary: This document contains technical descriptions and definitions related to AT&T's call detail records, including information on call types, originating and terminating numbers, and various identifiers used in mobile and wireline communications. It appears to be a technical report or internal document outlining how AT&T processes and categorizes call and data transactions.
keyFacts: The document provides detailed definitions of call types and features used by AT&T's network.
It explains the significance of various identifiers such as IMEI and IMSI in tracking mobile devices.
The document mentions that calls can traverse multiple networks, affecting how records are generated and reported.
It includes information on how AT&T handles data transactions over Wi-Fi and mobile networks.
There are references to specific call codes and their meanings, indicating the complexity of call processing.
